7. Explain the concept of Delgations in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Delegation means pushing data operations to the data source instead of bringing all the data into Power Apps.
ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps has a default limit of 500 records (we can increase upto max 2000 records).
ğŸ‘‰ When working with large datasets â€” for example, SharePoint lists with thousands of records.
ğŸ‘‰ So using non-delegable functions can cause some incorrect data results.
ğŸ‘‰ To problem slove this, we replaced non-delegable functions with delegable functions to handle data efficiently and correct data retrieval.
    ("Filter, Sort, and StartsWith")

ğŸ‘‰ This approach improved app speed, ensured data accuracy and delivers a better user experience.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

