10. Difference between Gallery, Form and Data Table?

âœ… GALLERY:
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Gallery is a control that used to display and interact with multiple records from a data source like SharePoint.
ğŸ‘‰ It support for dynamic layouts such as vertical, horizontal, and flexible-height galleries. 
ğŸ‘‰ In gallery, Each item can be customized using labels, images, icons, and buttons to create interactive views for users.

âœ… FORMS:
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Form is a control that used to view, create, and edit single record at a time from a connected data source.
ğŸ”¹ There are three types of forms:
1. Display Form â€“ for read-only data viewing.
2. Edit Form    â€“ for editing existing records.
3. New Form     â€“ for creating new records.
ğŸ‘‰ Forms can automatically generate fields based on the selected data source and handle data binding and submission with minimal configuration.
ğŸ‘‰ We can also customize field visibility, validation rules, and layout according to our needs.

âœ… DATA TABLE:
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Data Table is a control that used to display multiple records in a tabular format, similar to an Excel sheet.
ğŸ‘‰ It is mainly used for READ-ONLY data, where users need review the data, sorting, and scanning across rows and columns.
ğŸ‘‰ Data tables are automatically generates rows and columns based on the connected data source.
